(27, 'BAS Accounting', NULL, '13665090721737709502.png', '<h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:20pt\">Outsourced BAS/IAS Services for Small Businesses in Australia&nbsp;</span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Registered businesses that wish to comply with the Australian Tax Office (ATO) regulations must submit a BAS (Business Activity Statement) as part of the Goods and Service Tax regime. For the same reasons, businesses need outsourced BAS accounting services in Australia.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What is a Business Activity Statement?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">A BAS is a form that businesses fill out every year, depending on the size of their firm. The ATO utilises this information to calculate your GST refund. It also helps in calculating corporate income tax, fringe benefits tax, employee income tax, wine equalisation tax, luxury car tax, and fuel tax credits. BAS is a highlight of your company&#39;s financial transactions. The reports contain financial transactions that have tax contacts with the ATO, including:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:12pt\">Goods and Services Tax (GST)</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:12pt\">Pay as You Go (PAYG) instalments</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:12pt\">PAYG withholding tax</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:12pt\">Other taxes (FBT, FTC, etc</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">)</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">This report provides a summary of your company&#39;s financial performance. The ATO examines the information in your return to assess your tax position and determine whether you have additional responsibilities, such as luxury car tax. Such taxes are only a part of the taxes computed by BAS, including income, employment, wine, and petrol taxes. Because of the functions such taxes play, it is clear that there is a direct correlation between them and your company&#39;s overall financial situation based on the ATO-provided information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Businesses must prepare BAS monthly, quarterly, or annually, depending on their operations. You have to face legal challenges if you do not comply with the report preparation requirements. Businesses can outsource BAS accounting services to avoid legal consequences.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>How Does the BAS Work in Australia?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">When businesses file a BAS, they provide the ATO with a detailed record of their company&#39;s tax-related financial activities; reporting taxable purchases and sales is the top priority because it directly impacts their GST obligations.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">On the BAS form, you record the total amount of your taxable sales (items and services).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">s sold and subject to GST). You also report your taxable purchases (goods and services) you&#39;ve acquired that are subject to GST. This information is crucial for determining your net GST liability.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Our BAS Accounting and Bookkeeping Services:</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Our Business Activity Statement (BAS) accounting services include everything you need to be compliant in your business. We help you in managing BAS/IAS tax compliance and tax complications. Here at Aone Outsourcing Solutions, we provide the following BAS services:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>BAS Preparation</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">BAS preparation involves calculating GST, organising records, and verifying accuracy. Taking the help of BAS accountants can assist in preparing BAS statements. We help you</span><strong> prepare BAS by calculating GST, PAYG instalments, PAYG withholdings tax, and other taxes like FBT and FTC.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>BAS Filing and BAS Lodgement Process</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">After preparing all the records, you have to go through the BAS filing process according to ATO guidelines. BAS lodgement online refers to your official submission of BAS with the ATO, and missing penalties can result in significant fines and penalties. However, if you use professional BAS services like ours, we will do everything on schedule, allowing you to focus on your work.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>BAS Compliance &amp; BAS Support&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Small business operators have difficulties staying compliant with tax laws. Outsourcing BAS services can help you with BAS compliance seamlessly.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>GST and PAYG Compliance:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">At Aone Outsourcing Solutions, we make sure that your GST and PAYG compliance meets ATO guidelines. We help you in calculating, reporting, and recording all the transactions.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Instalment Activity Statement (IAS) Support&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">We also help you with your Instalment Activity Statement (IAS) by calculating PAYG and other withholding taxes. This pre-printed form is issued by ATO on a monthly basis and has a summary of your PAYG instalments, PAYG withholdings, and FBT obligations.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>How to Prepare Your BAS?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Before we go into how to deposit your BAS, let&#39;s go over how to prepare it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Here&#39;s a straightforward five-step approach for creating a firm Activity Statement (BAS) for a small firm in Australia:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Collect Records: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Gather all financial records from the reporting periods, such as invoices and receipts.</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Log In to the ATO Portal: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Access the ATO Business Portal and log in with your credentials.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Complete the BAS Form: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Complete the BAS form sections accurately, including GST, PAYG withholding, and other important information.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Review and Submit: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Double-check all figures and information for accuracy, then submit your BAS via the portal.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Payment (if applicable):&nbsp; </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Also, check if you have any due taxes; you should make the payment.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why is BAS Important for Australian Businesses?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">BAS is important for businesses in Australia, lets understand why:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Cash Flow:&nbsp; </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Your BAS provides a precise estimate of ATO reclaimable amounts. Having a good number helps you maintain healthy cash flow in your business.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Tax Calculation: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">BAS can calculate various taxes, including GST, employee-related, and industry-specific levies. It ensures that you fulfil all legal and tax obligations.</span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Business Insights: </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">A well-maintained BAS allows you to track vital insights into your firm, which are extremely useful when making future decisions.&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Legal Compliance:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">The ATO requires all qualifying firms to file their BAS on time. Failure to file BAS might result in legal compliance, including fines and penalties for your company.&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Procedure to Lodge BAS in Australia</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Businesses in Australia have to make sure to lodge their BAS and pay amounts on time. Here are the ways you can use to lodge your BAS:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Lodge BAS Online </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">Lodging your BAS lodgement online is flexible, and you can submit it according to your own schedule.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Additionally, there is a convenient two-week postponement option. This gives you an extra two weeks to lodge and pay your BAS, which can be quite useful.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">It&#39;s an excellent approach to avoiding errors. You can double-check everything before clicking the submit button to ensure that your results meet your expectations. Also, you can get assistance from the Outsourced BAS Lodgment service in Australia.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Lodge BAS by Mail </strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:11pt\">When submitting your completed BAS form, you can use the pre-addressed envelope included in your BAS package.</span></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Send your BAS to this address instead:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Australian Taxation Office</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Locked Bag 1936 Albury,&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>NSW 1936</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">If you have lost or never received your paper BAS, you can request a copy by calling us at </span><strong>13 28 66</strong><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Lodge BAS by BAS Agent</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">You can have a registered tax or BAS agent service manage the lodging, varying, and payment procedure for you via their preferred computerised platform.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">When you take this route:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Your agent can view any BAS and reminder communications sent to you via their web service.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">Even if your agent manages your BAS for you, you can still verify it yourself via online services for business or MyGov.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">If you need help finding a registered agent, visit the </span><strong>Tax Practitioners Board.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n	<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Lodge BAS &ldquo;NIL Using Phone</strong></h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:#000000; font-family:Roboto,sans-serif; font-size:11pt\">If you have nothing to report for the period and need to file a &#39;nil&#39; BAS, there&#39;s a convenient solution for that.</sp