compliance as they can get professional assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A professional BAS accounting service provider like Aone Outsourcing Solution in Australia can handle everything from BAS preparation to the BAS lodgement online process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>So, are you ready to simplify the BAS accounting process?&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Consider connecting with us and taking the first step toward hassle-free tax compliance and streamlined BAS accounting services.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>CTA: Contact Us Now</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 'bas-accounting-services-in-australia', NULL, NULL, 'Bas Accounting | Bas Lodgment | BAS Preparing Services in Australia', 'BASaccounting services, preparing BAS statements, BAS preparation, bas stands for, bas statement sole trader, bas accountants, BAS lodgment online, BAS Agent Services, Business Activity Statement, BAS Lodgement, BAS Compliance, bas lodgement service, bas agent services', 'We offer professional BAS accounting services, including BAS preparation, lodgement,  & compliance in AU. Ensure accurate and timely Business Activity Statement filing today!', 'Y', '2025-01-24 08:39:57', '2025-02-13 08:32:04', '20797357161738231080.png', '[{\"title\":\"What is a Business Activity Statement (BAS)?\",\"dec\":\"A Business Activity Statement (BAS) is a form that GST-registered businesses must submit to the Australian Taxation Office (ATO). It reports tax obligations, including GST, PAYG withholding, PAYG instalments, and other taxes.\"},{\"title\":\"Who needs to lodge a BAS in Australia?\",\"dec\":\"Any business registered for GST with a turnover of $75,000 or more ($150,000 for non-profits) must lodge a BAS. Businesses below this threshold do not need to register for GST or file BAS unless they choose to do so.\"},{\"title\":\"How often do I need to lodge my BAS?\",\"dec\":\"The BAS lodgement frequency depends on your business size and ATO requirements:\\r\\nMonthly\\u2014for businesses with GST turnover above $20 million.\\r\\nQuarterly\\u2014for most small to medium businesses.\\r\\nAnnually\\u2014If your business has voluntarily registered for GST and has a turnover below $75,000.\"},{\"title\":\"What happens if I miss the BAS lodgement deadline?\",\"dec\":\"Late lodgement can result in ATO penalties and interest charges. The fine starts at $275 for every 28-day delay, up to a maximum of $1,375. Outsourcing your BAS services ensures timely lodgement and avoids penalties.\"},{\"title\":\"What information is required for BAS preparation?\",\"dec\":\"To prepare a BAS, you need:\\r\\nTotal sales and income\\r\\nGST collected on sales\\r\\nGST paid on purchases\\r\\nPAYG withholding amounts (if applicable)\\r\\nOther tax obligations like luxury car tax or fringe benefits tax (FBT)\"},{\"title\":\"Can I correct an error in a lodged BAS?\",\"dec\":\"Yes! If you\\u2019ve made a mistake in your BAS, you can correct it in a future BAS if it\\u2019s within a four-year time limit. Otherwise, you may need to submit an amendment through the ATO portal or with a BAS agent\\u2019s help\"}]', 'Y', 'Y', 'Expertise in preparing and lodging Business Activity Statements (BAS) for businesses throughout Australia fits all business sizes.', 'BAS Accounting Services in Australia');
