(24, 'CV Madhukar', 'cv-madhukar', NULL, '1752909076.jpg', 'CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER', NULL, NULL, '<p>Madhukar leads Co-Develop, leveraging more than 25 years of experience in impact investing, policy, and scaling nonprofits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madhukar comes to Co-Develop from <a href=\"https://omidyar.com/\">Omidyar Network</a>, where as Managing Director he built out their global work on digital identity and digital public infrastructure. His previous experience includes setting up <a href=\"https://prsindia.org/\">PRS Legislative Research</a>, a research institution that focuses on making the legislative process in India better informed, more transparent, and participatory; working at the World Bank on issues regarding parliamentary capacity-building in various countries; and scaling some of India&rsquo;s largest nonprofits, including education nonprofit <a href=\"https://www.pratham.org/get-involved/opportunities\">Pratham</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madhukar was a Mason Fellow at the Harvard Kennedy School, where he earned his Master in Public Administration degree. He also has an MBA from the University of Houston and a Bachelor of Engineering degree from Bangalore University. He was elected as a Young Global Leader by the World Economic Forum, and is an Eisenhower Fellow, Ashoka Fellow, and an Echoing Green Fellow.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When he is not thinking about impact, Madhukar enjoys traveling with his family, watching movies, focusing on wellness, and dreaming of breaking the inertia to resume his amateur water-color painting interest.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:41:16', '2025-08-04 15:47:45', NULL, 'is_team'),
(25, 'Aaditya Rathour', 'aaditya-rathour', NULL, '1752909119.png', 'OPERATIONS ASSOCIATE', NULL, NULL, '<p>Aaditya is an Operations Associate at Co-Develop, where he manages the organization&#39;s operations and finances, ensuring smooth workflows and efficient financial management.With a strong background in project management, he has successfully overseen multiple grants and projects, streamlining processes and optimizing resource allocation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before joining Co-Develop, Aaditya was a Senior Funding &amp; Finance Associate at Good Business Lab, where he played a key role in managing GBL&#39;s extensive grants portfolio. His experience includes handling complex funding structures, compliance management, and financial oversight to support mission-driven initiatives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his free time, Aaditya enjoys watching football and playing games on his PS5.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:41:59', '2025-08-04 15:50:36', NULL, 'is_team'),
(26, 'Aura Cifuentes', 'aura-cifuentes', NULL, '1752909192.png', 'FELLOW - INVESTMENTS', NULL, NULL, '<p>Aura brings a dynamic blend of expertise in digital government, public innovation, and data-based public policy to CoDevelop.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She has public sector experience, having worked in France and Colombia for eight years. At <a href=\"https://www.etalab.gouv.fr/\" target=\"_blank\">Etalab</a>, Aura was crucial in advancing Open Data and Open Government initiatives. She served in the <a href=\"https://www.secretariatransparencia.gov.co/\" target=\"_blank\">Presidential Office</a>&nbsp;in Colombia, leading transparency and anti-corruption efforts. She&nbsp;designed and implemented Colombia&#39;s first public innovation policy at the National Planning Department. Most recently, as the Digital Government Director at the Colombian <a href=\"https://gobiernodigital.mintic.gov.co/portal/\" target=\"_blank\">Ministry of Technologies</a>, she spearheaded DPI projects that reached millions of citizens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the private sector, Aura&#39;s experience includes her role at <a href=\"https://www.inetum.com/fr\" target=\"_blank\">Inetum</a>, where she developed smart city strategies. She also served as Ecosystem Manager at <a href=\"https://agatadata.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Agata</a>, enhancing local government decision-making through data analytics. Additionally, she has worked as an international consultant with <a href=\"https://www.instiglio.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Instiglio</a>, designing the Global Effectiveness Network (GEN).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aura holds an MPA in Global Leadership from Columbia University, an MPA from Sciences Po, and a Bachelor&#39;s in Government and International Relations from Universidad Externado de Colombia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, she enjoys hiking with her Border Collie, practicing Pilates, and exploring the best wine bars in NYC. She is an advocate for women in STEM and frequently shares her insights through writing and speaking engagements.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:43:12', '2025-08-04 11:52:51', NULL, 'is_team'),
(27, 'Christine Kim', 'christine-kim', NULL, '1752909288.jpg', 'Director, Technology Adoption', NULL, NULL, '<p>Christine focuses on developing and operationalizing Co-Develop&rsquo;s investment strategy by identifying the most promising DPI technology adoption investments that can advance equitable economic growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Christine is a technology and international development professional with a decade of experience in strategy, program management, and stakeholder engagement to leverage technology for the public interest. She comes with practical field understanding of digital public infrastructure implementations, most recently having worked at <a href=\"https://www.simprints.com/\">Simprints</a>, the world&rsquo;s only nonprofit biometric ID company, where she facilitated multi-million dollar partnerships with <a href=\"https://www.gavi.org/\">Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance</a>, <a href=\"https://www.arm.com/\">Arm Ltd.</a>, the UK Foreign, Commonwealth, and Development Office, and more.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Christine has an MPhil in Development Studies (Economics focus) from the University of Cambridge and a BA Hons. in International Studies (Economics concentration) from Boston College.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of working hours, Christine enjoys reading fantasy novels, hiking the hills near her home, and watching film classics (her annual traditions include Parent Trap, Die Hard, and the Lord of the Rings trilogy).</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:44:48', '2025-08-04 15:54:37', NULL, 'is_team'),
(28, 'Desire Kachenje', 'desire-kachenje', NULL, '1752909422.png', 'SENIOR PRINCIPAL, INVESTMENTS - AFRICA', NULL, NULL, '<p>Desire Kachenje will be advancing Co-Develop&#39;s investment strategy by identifying and implementing the most promising digital public infrastructure investments in Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desire is a seasoned strategist in digital financial solutions and international development. Prior to Co-develop she was managing Grants and Partnerships at the Mojaloop Foundation. There, she forged key partnerships and managed projects that expanded financial inclusion. Notably, she pioneered an accelerator program that empowered local tech companies in Kenya, Zambia, Malawi, and Rwanda to deploy open-source, inclusive, real-time payment platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desire has also worked as a strategic consultant and innovation advisor at organizations like Deloitte Management Consulting and the World Food Programme (WFP). In these roles, she facilitated collaborations among government bodies, private sector entities, and developmental institutions, driving transformative changes in digital and economic landscapes to promote sustainable growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, Desire is passionate about the arts, enjoying dance and poetry, and is an avid reader who loves spending time on the beautiful beaches of East Africa.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:47:02', '2025-08-04 15:55:26', NULL, 'is_team'),
(29, 'Garikai Nhongo', 'garikai-nhongo', NULL, '1752909468.jpg', 'SENIOR COMMUNICATIONS MANAGER', NULL, NULL, '<p>Garikai oversees translating the ideas, work, and mission of Co-Develop into strategic messages that effectively engage key stakeholders and partners.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a communications strategist and global advocate, he is passionate about using the power of storytelling and collaboration to drive meaningful change. From high-level summits to grassroots initiatives, he thrives on connecting diverse perspectives and turning shared visions into transformative realities. His work spans continents, bridging cultures and fostering partnerships that amplify voices and inspire action. Whether crafting narratives, leading campaigns, or creating platforms for dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is a Communication and Stakeholder Management professional, having worked with 39 African countries, private sector companies and international partners to drive digital transformation across Africa. He joins Co-Develop from <a href=\"https://www.smartafrica.org/\">Smart Africa</a> where he led communication, marketing, private sector partnerships, and public sector stakeholder management. Garikai has also been the Team Leader for the European Union&rsquo;s Public Diplomacy and Strategic Communications in Rwanda and a key expert in the European Union&rsquo;s Public Diplomacy and Strategic Communications in Zimbabwe. He is also a board member for STEM for Development based in USA.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garikai holds a Master&rsquo;s in Public Administration, an MBA, a post-graduate diploma in Public Administration, and a BSc (Hon) Degree in Psychology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When he is not at work Garikai likes to write poetry and has published two books of poetry, which can be found online (upon request, Garikai may be willing to point readers in the right direction).</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-19 12:47:48', '2025-08-04 15:56:05', NULL, 'is_team'),
(30, 'Shikoh Gitau', 'shikoh-gitau', NULL, '1753937873.webp', 'Technical Advisor', NULL, NULL, '<p>Shikoh is the CEO of Qhala, a Digital Innovation company that catalyzes digital transformation capabilities for organizations across Africa. She has over 10 years of experience in the Research, Design, Implementation, and Management of Digital Technologies. She has established expertise in both African and Emerging Markets specialized in solving problems in Agriculture, Education, Health, Payments, Retail and Renewable energies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She is responsible for the set-up of Safaricom Alpha, a first of the kind corporate innovation hub in Africa. Where she worked as the Head of Products &ndash; Innovation and acted as the Chief Innovation Officer. Shikoh also led Safaricom&rsquo;s foray into becoming a digital company, by putting together a strategy, and cross-functional teams to execute the strategy. Dr. Shikoh has previously worked with Africa Development Bank (AfDB), where she was leading and advising governments across Africa to adopt ICT for service delivery, she developed the Digital Government Blueprint, a strategic document to guide governments in digital transformation, now adopted by Smart Africa. She has also worked with Google and Microsoft in their emerging markets teams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She has received numerous awards in recognition of her efforts in influencing Business and Government as well as Technology. Dr. Shikoh seats on various boards in ICT companies and contributes to a number of steering committees and think tanks on Africa and technology. Shikoh holds a PhD and MSc in Computer Science from the University of Cape Town, South Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Shikoh serves as an advisor to governments on matters of data and digital development.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-07-31 10:27:53', '2025-08-04 16:14:45', NULL, 'technical_adviser'),
(32, 'David Eaves', 'david-eaves', NULL, '1754286747.webp', 'Investment Committee', NULL, NULL, '<p>David seeks to provide conceptual frameworks of DPI, the challenges around governance for DPI and state capacity needed to create or implements DPIs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>David is an Associate Professor in Digital Government at the Institute for Innovation and Public Policy at University College London, where he teaches and writes on digital transformation and digital public infrastructure. As part of his work David co-hosts an annual convening of digital government leaders from around the world and has co-developed a course on digital-era public administration skills taught in over 20 universities. David works with governments around the world helping them think about their digital transformation strategies, including teaching thousands of senior public servants via executive education programs. Previously, David served as co-founder and CEO of <a href=\"https://recollect.net/\">ReCollect</a>, a civic tech start up that successfully grew to serve over 400 governments across North America and the UK. He has also worked with open source communities such as <a href=\"https://openmrs.org/\">OpenMRS</a>, <a href=\"https://www.drupal.org/\">Drupal</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.mozilla.org/\">Mozilla</a> in an effort to improve their collaboration capacity and enable them to further scale.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>David earned an MPhil in International Relations from the University of Oxford and a BA in History from Queen&rsquo;s University. In his spare time David loves playing ping pong with his kids, eating chocolate, and playing word games.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:22:27', '2025-08-04 16:08:22', NULL, 'investment_committee'),
(33, 'Liz Clyma', 'liz-clyma', NULL, '1754286877.webp', 'Investment Committee', NULL, NULL, '<p>Liz Clyma has spent her career formulating and operationalizing breakthrough strategies for some of the world&rsquo;s leading corporations and non-profit organizations. She specializes in structuring major investments for both commercial and social impact investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liz served over 10 years in leadership roles in the <a href=\"https://www.gatesfoundation.org/\">Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation</a>, developing and approving millions of dollars in philanthropic investments. Based in New Delhi as India Country Director for Health, she led integration of programming and $450M in grants to support India&rsquo;s achievement of UN Sustainable Development Goals. As CFO for the foundation&rsquo;s Global Health Division, she directed strategic and financial planning for deployment of $1.2B in annual charitable investments to combat infectious diseases disproportionately affecting the developing world. Previously, Liz was a Principal at <a href=\"https://www.bain.com/\">Bain &amp; Company</a>, where she specialized in corporate transformation, advising multi-national clients in the U.S. and Europe on strategy, operations, organization, and M&amp;A. Prior to Bain, Liz focused on private sector development in Russia and the former Soviet Union, both as an independent consultant and with the <a href=\"https://www.ifc.org/wps/wcm/connect/corp_ext_content/ifc_external_corporate_site/home\">IFC</a>, where she led the technical assistance and advisory services team for Financial Markets across the former USSR.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liz holds an MBA in Finance from Wharton Business School, an MA in Russian Area Studies and International Economics from the Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies, and a BA in Social Studies from Harvard University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liz enjoys outdoor sports and adventures with her husband and two darling daughters. In her spare time she&rsquo;s working on her personal Project 80 &ndash; how to live your 50s in a way that keeps you climbing mountains into your 80s.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:24:37', '2025-08-04 16:09:20', NULL, 'investment_committee'),
(34, 'Magdi M. Amin', 'magdi-m-amin', NULL, '1754286959.webp', 'Investment Committee', NULL, NULL, '<p>Magdi M. Amin is the Founder and Managing Partner of <a href=\"https://www.african-renaissance.com/\">African Renaissance Partners</a>, aninvestment and advisory firm focused on the Horn of Africa. African Renaissance Partners backs tech-focused entrepreneurs, seeking to use technology to solve major development challenges, such as access to finance, renewable energy, logistics, education, health, and agricultural productivity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Magdi is also an Adjunct Professor at the <a href=\"https://fpguide.foreignpolicy.com/2016-graduate-education/institutions/johns-hopkins-university-school-of-advanced-international-studies-sais/\">Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies</a>, teaching a graduate Practicum on Responsible Digital Development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previously, Magdi was Head of Corporate Strategy at the <a href=\"https://www.ifc.org/wps/wcm/connect/corp_ext_content/ifc_external_corporate_site/home\">IFC</a>, as well as numerous senior roles at the <a href=\"https://www.worldbank.org/en/home\">World Bank</a> in East Asia, Africa, and MENA. He was also Managing Director at <a href=\"https://omidyar.com/\">Omidyar Network</a> within the Responsible Technology practice before joining the Transitional Government of Sudan in January 2000 as a Senior Advisor to the Minister of Finance, where he supported economic reforms to stabilize the economy, regain access to multilateral financial institutions, restructure Sudan&rsquo;s external debt, and create broad-based growth. He led the design of the Sudan Family Support Program, a large cash transfer program that provided digital cash transfers to approximately five million Sudanese.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Magdi received an A.B. from Princeton and an M.A. from Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his spare time, Magdi writes on ancient Nubia, plays the saxophone, and is into CrossFit, though by no means actually fit.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:25:59', '2025-08-04 11:30:45', NULL, 'investment_committee'),
(35, 'Srikanth Nadhamuni', 'srikanth-nadhamuni', NULL, '1754287662.webp', 'Managing Trustee - eGovernments Foundation', NULL, NULL, '<p>Srikanth is a technologist and an entrepreneur with 35 years of experience in the areas of CPU (Central Processing Unit) design, Healthcare, National ID, Banking &amp; Financial Services sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is currently CEO of Khosla Labs, a startup incubator that he co-founded with Vinod Khosla, and chairman of Trustt. A Digital Banking SaaS company. He was on the Board of the HDFC Bank, the worlds 4th largest bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Srikanth was the founder CTO of Aadhaar, he led the setup of the Aadhaar Technology Center for the development, design and operations of the Aadhaar system to issue a National ID to all the 1.3 billion Indian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is also the Managing Trustee of the eGovernments Foundation which he co-founded with Nandan Nilekani(Chairman Infosys) in 2003. It focuses on improving governance and public service delivery in Indian cities using a suite of Municipal ERP products. Currently eGov products are deployed in over 2000 cities in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More recently during the Covid delta wave, Srikanth founded the 10BedICU project, to create ICUs in government hospitals in smaller towns and villages. 10BedICU has created over 200 10BedICUs in 8 states is less than 2yrs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Srikanth has spent 14 years in the Silicon Valley (California, US) working for several global companies such as Sun Microsystems (CPU design), Intel Corporation (CPU design), Silicon Graphics (Interactive TV) and WebMD (Internet Healthcare).</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:37:42', '2025-08-04 11:37:42', NULL, 'investment_committee'),
(37, 'Dasun Hegoda', 'dasun-hegoda', NULL, '1754287996.webp', 'Technical Advisor', NULL, NULL, '<p>Dasun works as a technical advisor for Co-Develop and offers technical advisory services focused on tech adoption strategies and conducts technical reviews throughout the investment due diligence process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dasun also serves as a Technical Advisor at the Presidential Secretariat of Sri Lanka, where he contributes his expertise to national digital transformation initiatives. With over many years of experience in enterprise application development and the digital arena, his career spans diverse leadership roles across both public and private sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previously, Dasun worked at Newlogic as an Enterprise Architect and Platform Evangelist, where he spearheaded the OpenSPP Digital Public Good (DPG). Prior to that, he held the position of Director/Software Architect at ICTA, the apex policy-making body guiding Sri Lanka&#39;s digital transformation efforts. He looked after key DPI projects for the Government of Sri Lanka, including National Digital Identity, National Fuel Pass, Digital Health Program, line of business solutions, etc. He was responsible for establishing a technical vision to deliver an innovative product/service in line with the business and technical requirements of the Government of Sri Lanka. Additionally, he has worked in multiple start-up companies in different capacities. Further, he worked as a visiting lecturer for the University of Kelaniya, Sri Lanka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He marked his entrance to the professional arena with a B.S. in Management Information Systems from the University of Dublin and an M.S. in Enterprise Application Development from Sheffield Hallam University. He&#39;s also a GovStack-certified architect. His special interests cover the areas of Digital Public Infrastructure, Digital Public Goods, and Enterprise Architecture &amp; Design.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work,&nbsp;Dasun likes to play badminton and experience new foods in his leisure time.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:39:24', '2025-08-04 16:13:24', NULL, 'technical_adviser'),
(38, 'Rosa Akbari', 'rosa-akbari', NULL, '1754287860.webp', 'Technical Advisor', NULL, NULL, '<p>Rosa Akbari is an independent consultant working on digitalization within humanitarian contexts, with a special focus on cash transfers. <a href=\"https://rakbari.com/\">Rosa</a> has worked at the intersection of humanitarian response and technology since 2009, having previously worked for Mercy Corps, the International Rescue Committee (<a href=\"http://www.rescue.org/\">IRC</a>), World Food Programme (WFP), <a href=\"http://www.dimagi.com/\">Dimagi</a>, and the public sector. She currently advises donors, implementers, service providers, and research on topics ranging from payments, data management, and interoperability in complex operating contexts, for crisis affected populations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2012, Rosa conducted independent research piloting SMS-based feedback loops in the Western Sahara refugee camps as an inaugural grantee of UNOCHA&rsquo;s Humanitarian Futures programme. Her career began, however, as a civilian research assistant at the Naval Postgraduate School, supporting field experiments and cross-industry collaborations for humanitarian assistance &amp; disaster relief - including deployment for the 2010 Haitian Earthquake response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, Rosa supports&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.omgyno.com/\">Omgyno</a>, a Healthtech startup, and enjoys uncovering her next favourite taverna.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:41:00', '2025-08-04 16:13:59', NULL, 'technical_adviser'),
(39, 'Lisette Solis', 'lisette-solis', NULL, '1754287913.webp', 'Technical Advisor', NULL, NULL, '<p>Lisette is a technical advisor specializing in data governance, AI, and civic technology. She most recently worked for the Responsible AI Division at the Department of Defense, where she helped define federal policy on AI use and developed tools to help staff better understand AI risks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With nearly a decade of experience in international development, Lisette has worked at the intersection of technology and social impact across multiple organizations. At the Development Innovation Lab, she researched the impact of innovations and technology in the developing world. She has also worked for the United Nations, Fair Trade USA, and the non-profit, blueEnergy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lisette holds a Master of Science in Computational Analysis and Public Policy from the University of Chicago&#39;s computer science department and a Bachelor of Arts in Environmental Economics from UC Berkeley.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, Lisette enjoys swimming and exploring New York City where she lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 11:41:53', '2025-08-04 16:15:16', NULL, 'technical_adviser'),
(40, 'Jordan Sandman', 'jordan-sandman', NULL, '1754303238.webp', 'Principal, Investments', NULL, NULL, '<p>Jordan leads Co-Develop&rsquo;s&nbsp;research grantmaking and serves as an investment lead for civil society grantmaking. He is building a movement of policy experts and researchers to support the development and deployment of safe, inclusive digital public infrastructure in countries across the world.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHe is an investments principal with a background in research and advocacy for technology as a tool for social development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jordan is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of the University of Michigan&rsquo;s Gerald R. Ford School of Public Policy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outside of work, Jordan enjoys playing in and attending sporting events, reading, writing, and hiking.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 15:57:18', '2025-08-04 15:57:18', NULL, 'is_team'),
(41, 'Lindsey Crumbaugh', 'lindsey-crumbaugh', NULL, '1754303378.webp', 'CHIEF INVESTMENTS OFFICER', NULL, NULL, '<p>Lindsey leads the investment team and process for identifying, funding, and supporting a global portfolio of high-impact DPI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Throughout her career, Lindsey has invested in and scaled nonprofits and social enterprises. Most recently she was a Managing Director at <a href=\"https://npxadvisors.com/\" target=\"_blank\">NPX</a>, where she developed innovative financial products that linked financial and social returns. Prior to NPX, Lindsey was the Managing Director and VP of Strategy &amp; Development at <a href=\"https://www.sama.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sama</a>, a B-Corp focused on inclusive AI, where she developed and scaled new growth initiatives and oversaw the company&rsquo;s nonprofit program. Before Sama, Lindsey worked at the <a href=\"https://www.clintonhealthaccess.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Clinton Health Access Initiative</a> in Zambia serving as the Deputy Country Director and Senior Program Manager for the Human Resources for Health program focused on increasing access to health services across the country.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lindsey started her career in finance, working in private equity and investment banking. She holds an MBA from Harvard Business School and a BS in Applied Economics &amp; Management from Cornell University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In her free time, Lindsey enjoys hiking and working on her lifelong pursuit to cook &ldquo;guest-appropriate&rdquo; dishes. She lives in Atlanta with her partner and their two children.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 15:59:38', '2025-08-04 15:59:38', NULL, 'is_team'),
(42, 'Liz Ramey', 'liz-ramey', NULL, '1754303476.webp', 'DIRECTOR, OPERATIONS', NULL, NULL, '<p>Liz Ramey leads Operations at Co-Develop, crafting organizational systems and processes that allow us to operate efficiently and that ground our work in the principles of diversity, equity, and inclusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Liz is passionate about inclusive development and good governance in the U.S. and around the globe, and has worked to advance that through positions with the <a href=\"https://civiliansinconflict.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Center for Civilians in Conflict</a>, <a href=\"https://indivisible.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Indivisible</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.wilsoncenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars</a>, <a href=\"https://www.vitalvoices.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Vital Voices</a>, the Civil Service Agency of the Government of Liberia, and the <a href=\"https://www.ifpri.org/\" target=\"_blank\">International Food Policy Research Institute</a>. Early in her career, she spent two years developing adult education programs in Nairobi, Kenya, and still speaks advanced Swahili. She is also a proud board member of <a href=\"https://www.ideasgeneration.org/\" target=\"_blank\">IDEAS Generation</a>, a network of NextGen leaders advancing inclusion, diversity, equity, accessibility, and social justice. Liz holds an M.P.A. in International Affairs from Princeton University, an M.Sc. in African Studies from the University of Oxford, and a B.A. in Economics and Sociology from The George Washington University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When not pondering how to make systems work for people, Liz enjoys watching classic films, wandering around cities, and aspiring to be a Food Network chef (Alton Brown and Marcus Samuelsson are two of her culinary icons).</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:01:16', '2025-08-04 16:01:16', NULL, 'is_team'),
(43, 'Matthew McNaughton', 'matthew-mcnaughton', NULL, '1754303575.webp', 'Director -  Inclusion, Safety & Civil Society Engagement !', NULL, NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Matthew McNaughton is a digital development practitioner from Kingston, Jamaica. At Co-Develop he leads the organization&rsquo;s civil society engagement in the shaping of digital public infrastructure initiatives in partner countries. Matthew develops strategies and leads projects that focus on practical applications of digital technology, service design, and citizen participation in governance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Before CoDevelop, Matthew worked at UNICEF as a Global Technology For Development Specialist, where he oversaw a digital messaging ecosystem that delivered more than 490 million messages each year connecting children, mothers, and caregivers with life-saving information and public services. Matthew also spent 3 years at the World Bank as an Open Innovation Specialist, where he led a number of open government and citizen feedback programs in Nigeria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In his personal capacity Matthew actively engages in shaping the building blocks of digital society emerging in Jamaica and the Caribbean. He co-founded the SlashRoots Foundation, a social impact organization utilizing digital practices to improve the design and delivery of public services and development programs in the Caribbean, convened civil society-private sector contributions to data protection and digital identity legislation, and serves on multiple boards, including Jamaica&rsquo;s Open Government Partnership (OGP) Multi-Stakeholder Forum and on the Board of Directors for the Caribbean Open Institute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Matthew held Edward S. Mason and Ash Democracy Fellowships at the Harvard Kennedy School, where he earned his Master in Public Administration, and a B.A in Philosophy from the College of Wooster. When he isn&rsquo;t thinking about how digital can improve public services, he&rsquo;s likely following the latest Liverpool FC news.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:02:55', '2025-08-04 17:35:25', NULL, 'is_team'),
(44, 'Robert Karanja', 'robert-karanja', NULL, '1754303640.webp', 'Senior Director, Africa', NULL, NULL, '<p>Robert leads Co-Develop&rsquo;s investments and strategic partnerships in Africa working closely with the global investments team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Robert is passionate about responsible technology and previously led the Omidyar Network&rsquo;s portfolio of investments in Digital Identity. At Omidyar his investment strategy included working closely with governments, multilateral agencies, civil society, and research institutions that explored exciting areas of work, including encrypted messaging platforms, data privacy, digital rights, digital transformation, and e-government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Robert also currently serves as an Advisory Council Member for California State University&rsquo;s Cybersecurity Program. The council works collaboratively to provide constructive feedback and strategic direction to guide quality improvement and assess program efficacy. He serves on various boards including B Lab East Africa and Select Africa Limited where he provides strategic and advisory oversight to both organizations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Robert holds an MBA in Strategic Management from Moi University and a BCom in Entrepreneurship from the University of Northern British Columbia. In his spare time Robert is an avid golfer, ice hockey fan, and loves spending time with his sons.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:04:00', '2025-08-04 16:04:00', NULL, 'is_team'),
(45, 'Sourav Das', 'sourav-das', NULL, '1754303704.webp', 'Associate - Investments', NULL, NULL, '<p>Sourav is an Associate on the Investments team at Co-Develop. Before joining Co-Develop, he was a Senior Associate at IDinsight, where he gained extensive experience generating data in key policy areas with governments and not-for-profits, and collaborating with them to encourage the use of evidence in decision-making. He is particularly interested in the intersection between technology, governance, and livelihoods. Sourav has also completed the prestigious LAMP fellowship, supporting a Member of Parliament in India on legislative issues and stakeholder management.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSourav received an undergraduate degree in Economics from the University of Delhi and a Master&#39;s in Public Policy from the National Law School of India University, Bangalore.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn his free time, Sourav enjoys reading, dancing, playing football, and cooking new recipes. He also enjoys walking around cities and doing street photography.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:05:04', '2025-08-04 16:05:04', NULL, 'is_team'),
(46, 'Tim Wood', 'tim-wood', NULL, '1754303765.webp', 'Chief Partnerships Officer', NULL, NULL, '<p>Tim leads Co-Develop&rsquo;s global partnerships and strategy for DPI in Health. Tim joined Co-Develop after nine years at the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation where he defined digital health investment strategies, worked closely with country partners to implement digital systems, shaped and managed investments, and led global initiatives to coordinate funding across multiple donor agencies. He is a widely recognized and trusted thought leader in digital public infrastructure, catalyzing and co-authoring the <a href=\"https://digitalprinciples.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Principles of Digital Development</a> and the <a href=\"https://digitalinvestmentprinciples.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Principles of Donor Alignment for Digital Health</a>, as well as serving on the board for multiple organizations including <a href=\"https://digitalsquare.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Digital Square</a> and <a href=\"https://dial.global/\" target=\"_blank\">DIAL</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previously, Tim spent 12 years at Microsoft working on software development and 12 years at the Grameen Foundation&rsquo;s Technology Center. While with Grameen Foundation, Tim pioneered replication of the Grameen Village Phone program, launching sustainable initiatives in Uganda and Rwanda and co-authoring the Village Phone Replication Manual. Tim went on to implement money pilot programs for microfinance institutions in the Philippines and Kenya and initiated Grameen Foundation&rsquo;s efforts in the health sector. As the Director of Mobile Health Innovation at the Grameen Foundation, he built a team that creating the open-source MOTECH software platform to deliver multiple mobile-phone based service initiatives at scale in India and Africa. Tim has a B.A. in Political Science from Stanford University and spends most of his spare time on a bicycle.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:06:05', '2025-08-04 16:06:05', NULL, 'is_team'),
(47, 'Yasodara Córdova', 'yasodara-cordova', NULL, '1754304104.webp', 'Investment Committee', NULL, NULL, '<p><span style=\"font-family:Poppins,sans-serif\">Yasodara, or Yaso, is a technologist with 18+ years of experience working at the intersection of research, public policy, and product management, focusing on privacy, security, and ethics in A.I. Currently, she is the head of Privacy Research at a Brazilian unicorn, <a href=\"https://unico.io/\">unico IDtech</a>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Poppins,sans-serif\">She is a former Mason fellow with the <a href=\"https://ash.harvard.edu/\">Ash Center for Democratic Governance and Innovation</a> at Harvard University. Before the Ash Center fellowship, she assisted countries in integrating technology into their governance infrastructure as an agile/citizen engagement fellow at the <a href=\"https://www.worldbank.org/en/home\">World Bank</a>&#39;s governance sector. Her work at the institution went from helping governments develop infrastructure for participatory platforms to stemming corruption among civil servants using emerging tools. She is a former Senior Fellow of the <a href=\"https://projects.iq.harvard.edu/digitalhks/home\">Digital Kennedy School</a> and a former fellow and affiliate of the <a href=\"https://cyber.harvard.edu/\">Berkman Klein Center for Internet and Society</a> at Harvard University. Yaso was part of the <a href=\"https://ciudadaniai.org/\">Ciudadania Inteligente&#39;s</a> Director&#39;s board and is the former CEO of the &quot;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Serenata_de_Amor\">Serenata de Amor Operation</a>,&quot; an anti-corruption A.I. platform that uses machine learning and open data to facilitate social control money spent by representatives in Brazil. Before being selected as a Fellow of the Berkman Klein Center in 2016, Yasodara worked as a Web Specialist at the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/\">World Wide Web Consortium</a>, building standards for the web and leading the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/2015/spatial/\">Data on the Web Working Group</a>.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Poppins,sans-serif\">In her early life, she worked with citizen journalism and was twice awarded the most prominent Brazilian prize in Journalism and Human Rights, the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vladimir_Herzog_Award\">Vladimir Herzog Award</a>. She is the first female Hackerspace founder in Brazil and was part of the <a href=\"https://okfn.org/\">Open Knowledge Foundation</a> advisory board from its outset in Brazil until 2018.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Poppins,sans-serif\">Yaso holds a Master&#39;s in Public Administration from the Kennedy School of Government at Harvard, an MBA from FGV - Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o Getulio Vargas, and a BA in Design from Universidade de Bras&iacute;lia.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Y', '2025-08-04 16:11:32', '2025-08-04 19:44:39', NULL, 'investment_committee');

